Series I: Rufus King, Letters sent to Nicholas Low, 1790-1823

The naval battle led by Admiral Nelson and the observation that the British are "now entire masters of the Mediterranean" and how that relates to the fate of Napoleon; France and Austria in conflict; Turks and Russians against the French; Thomas Paine's advice on how to pursue an attack against the United States; rebellion in Ireland
